name: 80s Movie Poster Style (LORA)
description:
(v1.5 UPDATE): Fixed the Network Rank and Network Dimensions to be 128 now.

Hello there! I've created a LoRA based on 17 movie poster images from the 1980s and 2 epochs!

I've compiled multiple movie posters of E.T., Star Wars, Back to the Future, etc.

I absolutely love the grainy realistic oil painting/aesthetic that 80s movie posters (usually) had and I wanted to see if I can replicate that through a LoRA.

Recommended LoRA weight: ~0.9-1.0

Recommended sizes: either 512x768 or 768x1024 if you want a similar dimension to the actual movie posters

Recommended checkpoints to use: Deliberate and Dreamshaper (but you can experiment with others if you'd like)

Make sure you add the trigger word "80s movie poster" in your prompt

You can also add the keywords "on the top", "on the middle", and "on the bottom" if you want to place certain images in a particular area as well.

Enjoy!

modelVersions.name: v1.5
modelVersions.description: Fixed the Network Rank and Network Dimension to be over 128
